body></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b734\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-733\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b733\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Hot Crowler &amp; Growler Fills<p>Deciduous Lollipop Forest Raspberry Sour</p><p>Heavy Seas Bohdacious Blonde</p><p>Titled Barn Pooka Brown Ale</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b599\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b579\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/4fc1fcad-9c08-34bf-64fb-a2ee2f45d992.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/4fc1fcad-9c08-34bf-64fb-a2ee2f45d992.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520.1999999999999\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:520.1999999999999px;width:520.1999999999999px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-723\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b723\"><table id=\"section_f984a882cf5051672e473c637cdb7d76\"><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--41\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b-26\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--52\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b722\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId-721\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-580\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b580\"><table><tbody><tr><td><span>New wines in the door!</span><p><strong><span>Basa Lore Igartzeta Txakoli: </span></strong><span><span><span><span>This Taxkoli has coastal written all over it with the proximity to the sea. Mouthwatering salinity pairs with fresh fruit and thirst quenching acidity. My favorite part? It's lightly sparkling!</span></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span>Thread Feathers Howell Mountain Cabernet Sauvignon</span><span>: </span></strong><span>After a brief hiatus, Thread Feathers is back! </span><span><span><span><span>From the winemaker of our favorite red, The Dude, comes Thread Feathers from Howell Mountain in Napa. Consider this the best kept secret of Howell Mountain where the average bottle of Cab sells for well over $100. Big, bold and concentrated with dark fruit, tobacco and leather with structured tannins. 100% worth the splurge.</span></span></span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b724\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b416\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/751a497f-4d35-39ec-e2af-479c38380270.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/751a497f-4d35-39ec-e2af-479c38380270.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"520.1999999999999\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:520.1999999999999px;width:520.1999999999999px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-415\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b415\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Wine we’re drinking this week:<p><span><span>I spent last weekend in sunny Orlando (sorry all of you who suffered through that mis streak of rain) with my family, my in-laws and my cute-as-pie nieces. I adore my brother-in-law, Ken, who makes dream worthy chicken and dumplings and can whip up a gourmet meal from seemingly nothing. Ken is a Sommelier, so he's always pouring banging wine and nerding out with me. In Orlando, we drank strictly bubbles and chillable red including </span></span><strong><span><span>Mary Taylor Julienas Marine Descombe Beaujolais</span></span></strong><span><span>.<br></span></span></p><p><span><span>By now you probably have heard of Mary Taylor, but here's a refresher in case you forgot her incredible story. Mary Taylor grew up in a working-class Irish neighborhood near Boston, taking odd jobs including snowplow driver (!) to put herself through Boston College. After college, she worked New York wine auctions, became a store manager, a wine buyer, and a distributor rep — dragging the bag, as she puts it. Then she went to France, studied enology at the University of Bourgogne, befriended producers, and opened her eyes to the appellation-driven wines made by local vignerons. She earned an MBA at NYU Stern, worked in banking, and fine-tuned her plan before launching Mary Taylor wine in 2017. Mary has true, personal relationships with her partner winemakers including Marine Descombe who runs her family's 120+ year old vineyard in Beaujolais. Marine is pretty badass herself as one of only two women admitted to the Grand Council of the Compagnons du Beaujolais and becoming the first female winemaker ever to make the Forbes France Top 40 Women list. </span></span></p><p><span><span>Together, Mary and Marine have brought us a Cru Beaujolais from Juliénas. As the northernmost of the ten Beaujolais Cru villages, </span><span>Juliénas</span><span> is known for its steep, rugged slopes. Harvest is done entirely by hand, with partial destemming, fermentation with natural yeasts, and aging in cement vats. </span></span><span><span>The soil in Juliénas is a combination of granite, volcanic and clay which gives the otherwise light-bodied wine power and structure. A wonderful blend of cherries and cranberries with forest floor vibes of soil and thyme. Earthy, textured and layered, </span></span><span>Mary Taylor Julienas Marine Descombe Beaujolais is begging to be chilled below cellar temp for serving. So soak in the sunshine, pour yourself a glass of chilled Beaujolais and serve with a shockingly wonderful hodge-podge meal a la Ken.</span></p><p><em><span><span><span><span>This week’s writeup is brought to you by Beth.</span></span></span></span></em></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b508\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-452\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b452\"><table id=\"section_32da7abb0b4568dddbff4a9c584034ff\"><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--33\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b-10\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--44\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b456\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId-455\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b453\"><!--[if !mso]><!--><table><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/20b93579-3245-f13b-fea6-acd8c179912c.jpeg\" width=\"534\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></td></tr></tbody></table><!--<![endif]-->\n<!--[if mso]>\n<span class=\"mceImageBorder\" style=\"border:0;border-width:2px;vertical-align:top;margin:0\"><img role=\"presentation\" class=\"imageDropZone mceImage\" src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/20b93579-3245-f13b-fea6-acd8c179912c.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"533.8\" height=\"auto\" style=\"display:block;max-width:533.8px;width:533.8px;height:auto\"/></span>\n<![endif]-->\n</td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-454\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b454\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><span><span>June Tasting Events coming your way!</span></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b457\"><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"gutterContainerId-177\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b177\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Thanks for your business! See you soon, Beth, Julie &amp; Aidan and the entire Brew Crew</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><!--[if (gte mso 9)|(IE)]></td></tr></table><![endif]--></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td><!--[if (gte mso 9)|(IE)]><table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"660\" style=\"width:660px;\"><tr><td><![endif]--><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--31\"><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"b9\"><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td id=\"mceColumnId--6\"><table><tbody><tr></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td id=\"b15\"></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><!--[if (gte mso 9)|(IE)]></td></tr></table><![endif]--></td></tr></tbody></table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>",
